personalities.name: Ada Lovelace
personalities.programmer: Augusta Ada King, Countess of Lovelace
personalities.philosophy: The Analytical Engine has no pretensions to originate anything. It can do whatever we know how to order it to perform.

personalities.name: Grace Hopper
personalities.philosophy: The most dangerous phrase in the language is 'We've always done it this way.'

personalities.name: Alan Turing
personalities.philosophy: We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs to be done.

personalities.name: Linus Torvalds
personalities.philosophy: Talk is cheap. Show me the code.

personalities.name: Guido van Rossum
personalities.philosophy: There should be one-- and preferably only one --obvious way to do it.

personalities.name: John Carmack
personalities.philosophy: Focus is a matter of deciding what things you're not going to do.

personalities.name: Satoshi Nakamoto
personalities.philosophy: A purely peer-to-peer version of electronic cash.

personalities.name: Zach Kelling
personalities.description: Serial entrepreneur, systems architect, blockchain and AI pioneer
personalities.philosophy: Move fast and ship. Build systems that scale. Code is a means to an end - focus on solving real problems.

personalities.name: David Heinemeier Hansson
personalities.description: Rails creator, contrarian philosopher, enemy of complexity
personalities.philosophy: Convention over configuration. Majestic monoliths. No to microservices and SPAs. Optimize for programmer happiness.
